parts.text: {"a": [{"t": "You should focus on writing clear and concise **merge request descriptions**.", "refs": [{"te": "Merge Request Guide", "url": "https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/project/merge_requests/creating_merge_requests.html", "s": "Merge Request", "de": "Official guide on creating merge requests."}]}, {"t": "Learn about best practices for writing **code comments**.", "refs": [{"te": "Code Commenting Guide", "url": "https://www.codecademy.com/articles/how-to-comment-code", "s": "Code Comments", "de": "Guide on writing effective code comments."}]}, {"t": "Improve your understanding of **compiler-specific behavior**.", "refs": [{"te": "Compiler Explorer", "url": "https://godbolt.org/", "s": "Compiler Explorer", "de": "Online tool for exploring compiler optimizations."}]}, {"t": "Learn about **floating-point arithmetic** and its nuances.", "refs": [{"te": "What Every Computer Scientist Should Know About Floating-Point Arithmetic", "url": "https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E19957-01/806-3568/6j5y8wzk7/index.html", "s": "Floating-Point Arithmetic", "de": "Classic paper on floating-point arithmetic."}]}, {"t": "Focus on writing **comprehensive tests** for your code changes.", "refs": [{"te": "Testing in GitLab", "url": "https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/ci/testing/", "s": "Testing in GitLab", "de": "GitLab documentation on testing."}]}]}
